        content: '<h3>Sharing LIs and SCs</h3><p>Share LIs and SCs at the start of the lesson—visually (board, slide) and verbally. Do not assume pupils will remember from last time. Refer back during the lesson: "Which success criterion are you working on?" "How will you show me you have met it?"</p><p>Use them to structure plenaries: "Show me you have met the success criteria." "Thumbs up if you have met the first criterion."</p><h3>Linking to EXA Es+Os</h3><p>In BGE, link LIs and SCs to Experiences and Outcomes where appropriate. In Drama, EXA 3-12a relates to creating and presenting drama. Your SCs for a performance task should align with what that outcome expects. In Art, EXA 3-02a, 3-03a relate to responding and creating. In Photography, similar links apply.</p><p>This makes assessment transparent: pupils see how their work connects to the curriculum. It also supports consistency across the department.</p><h3>Senior Phase</h3><p>For N4, N5, Higher, link to course requirements and assessment standards. SCs for portfolio work should reflect the criteria pupils will be judged on.</p><h3>Key Takeaway</h3><p>Share at the start. Refer during. Use in plenaries. Link to Es+Os and assessment. Make the learning journey visible.</p>',
