        content: '<h3>Drama</h3><p>Retrieve: key vocabulary (proxemics, blocking, levels, gesture, stimulus, conventions, mood, atmosphere), differences between terms (gesture vs. movement, scripted vs. devised), stages of devising. Use "What is the term for...?" or "What is the difference between...?" Flashcards with term on one side, definition on the other. Quick rounds: "One Drama term—go!"</p><h3>Art & Design</h3><p>Retrieve: elements of art (line, shape, colour, tone, texture, form), colour theory (primary, secondary, complementary, analogous), composition (rule of thirds, balance, focal point). "Draw the colour wheel." "Name three elements you used in your last piece."</p><h3>Photography</h3><p>Retrieve: exposure triangle (aperture, shutter, ISO), depth of field, rule of thirds, leading lines, framing. "What does aperture control?" "What happens when you increase ISO?" Label diagrams. Quick quizzes on camera settings.</p><h3>Building a Habit</h3><p>Make retrieval a regular part of your lessons. Once it is routine, pupils expect it and engage more readily. Vary the format to keep it fresh.</p>',
